🍕 Pizza Sales Performance Analysis & BI Dashboard
📌 Project Overview
This project presents a 1-year business performance analysis of a pizza company using data analytics and business intelligence dashboards.

The goal is to transform raw transactional data into actionable insights that help stakeholders understand:

Revenue trends

Product performance

Customer behavior

Overall business growth

🎯 Problem Statement
After completing its first year of operations, the business lacked a centralized analytical view to evaluate performance.

Key questions included:

How did the business perform financially?

Which products drive the most revenue?

What are the customer purchasing patterns?

How does sales vary across time?

Where can improvements be made?

🎯 Objectives
Build a comprehensive performance dashboard system

Provide an executive-level summary

Identify top & bottom-performing products

Analyze customer behavior patterns

Generate data-driven business insights

📂 Data Source & Structure
Data Source: Excel Workbook

Data Type:

Fact Table → Sales Transactions

Dimension Tables → Products, Customers, Store, Expenses

🧩 Data Model
Star schema-based model

Relationships established between fact and dimension tables

Optimized for filtering and reporting

🧹 Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
Performed the following steps:

Handled missing values

Removed duplicates

Corrected data types

Validated relationships

Created calculated fields & KPIs

📊 Key Metrics Created
Revenue

Average Order Value (AOV)

Contribution %

Growth %

KPI Measures using DAX

